description:
drh added on 2013-01-03 15:27:36:
The following SQL run in a shell generates an assertion fault in the name
resolution logic:
ATTACH ':memory:' AS aux1;
CREATE TABLE t1(a,b); INSERT INTO t1 VALUES(222,'x2');
CREATE TABLE main.t2(a,b); INSERT INTO main.t2 VALUES(444,'x4');
CREATE TABLE aux1.t2(a,b); INSERT INTO aux1.t2 VALUES(555,'x5');
SELECT *
  FROM t1 JOIN (main.t2 JOIN aux.t2 ON aux.t2.a=main.t2.a+111)
            ON main.t2.a=t1.a+222;
This fault has been present in the code since version 3.6.2, 2008-08-30.  The 
fault appears to have been injected by check-in [daf730d1defa78fb8b8].  Prior
to that check-in, the SQL above would throw an error: 
"no such table: aux.t4".  So it appears that no prior version of SQLite would
get the correct answer to the SQL above.
